== Deaths == * [[Yōshō (Southern Song)|Yōshō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[422]] [[:en:June 27|June 27]]) – Emperor Wu of the Southern Song (【劉裕】), the first Emperor of the Song dynasty (born [[356]]). * Shōkyō 2nd year / Genkō 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1333|1333]] [[:en:July 4|July 4]]) – [[:en:Hōjō Mototoki|Hōjō Motoki]], the 13th Shikken of the Kamakura shogunate (born [[:en:1285|1285]]). * Shōkyō 2nd year / Genkō 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1333|1333]] [[:en:July 4|July 4]]) – [[:en:Hōjō Takatoki|Hōjō Takatoshi]], the 14th Shikken of the Kamakura shogunate and 9th Detsū (born [[:en:1303|1303]]). * Shōkyō 2nd year / Genkō 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1333|1333]] [[:en:July 4|July 4]]) – [[:en:Hōjō Sadaaki|Hōjō Sadakazu]], the 15th Shikken of the Kamakura shogunate (born [[:en:1278|1278]]). * [[Ryakuō]] 1st year / [[Engen]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1338|1338]] [[:en:June 10|June 10]]) – [[:en:Kitabatake Akiie|Kitabatake Akiie]], a military commander ({{ill|Busho (Rank)|ja|武将|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Busho (Rank)|qq=}}) (born [[:en:1318|1318]]). * [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 14th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1586]] [[:en:July 8|July 8]]) – [[:en:Hachisuka Masakatsu|Hachisuga Masakatsu]], a military commander (born [[1526]]). * [[Tenna]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1682]] [[:en:June 27|June 27]]) – [[:en:Ikeda Mitsumasa|Ikeda Mitsumasa]], lord of the Okayama Domain in Bizen (born [[1609]]). * [[:en:Hōei|Hōei]] 7th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1710]] [[:en:June 18|June 18]]) – {{ill|Kawai Sōrō|ja|河合曾良|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kawai Sōrō|qq=}}, a haiku poet and one of the disciples of Shōmon Jūtetsu (born [[1649]]). * [[Kansei]] 11th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1799]] [[:en:June 25|June 25]]) – [[:en:Asada Goryu|Asada Gōritsu]], an astronomer (born [[1734]]).
