== Events == * [[:en:Tengyō|Tenkei]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:938|938]] [[:en:June 22|June 22]]) – The era name was changed from [[:en:Jōhei|Shōhei]] to [[:en:Tengyō|Tenkei]]. * [[:en:Shōkyō|Shōkyō]] 2nd year / [[:en:Genkō|Genkō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1333|1333]] [[:en:July 4|July 4]]) – The Kamakura shogunate was overthrown when [[Nitta Yoshisada]] attacked Kamakura, forcing about 800 members of the [[:en:Later Hōjō clan|Later Hōjō clan]] clan, including [[:en:Hōjō Takatoki|Hōjō Takatoshi]], to commit suicide.
== Births == * Genbun 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1737|1737]] [[:en:June 20|June 20]]) – [[:en:Tokugawa Ieharu|Tokugawa Ieharu]], the 10th shōgun of the Tokugawa shogunate (died [[:en:1786|1786]]). * [[:en:Bunka|Bunka]] 12nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1815|1815]] [[:en:June 29|June 29]]) – {{ill|Asada Sōhaku|ja|浅田宗伯|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Asada Sōhaku|qq=}}, a physician of traditional Chinese medicine and Confucian scholar ({{ill|Ru|ja|儒学者|zh|儒生|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ru|qq=}}) (died [[:en:1894|1894]]). * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 6th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1859|1859]] [[:en:June 22|June 22]]) – {{ill|Tsubouchi Shōyō|ja|坪内逍遙|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsubouchi Shōyō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 坪内逍遥}}, a novelist (died [[:en:1935|1935]]).
== Deaths == * [[Yōshō (Southern Song)|Yōshō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:422|422]] [[:en:June 27|June 27]]) – Emperor Wu of the Southern Song (【劉裕】), the first Emperor of the Song dynasty (born [[:en:356|356]]). * Shōkyō 2nd year / Genkō 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1333|1333]] [[:en:July 4|July 4]]) – [[:en:Hōjō Mototoki|Hōjō Motoki]], the 13th Shikken of the Kamakura shogunate (born [[:en:1285|1285]]). * Shōkyō 2nd year / Genkō 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1333|1333]] [[:en:July 4|July 4]]) – [[:en:Hōjō Takatoki|Hōjō Takatoshi]], the 14th Shikken of the Kamakura shogunate and 9th Detsū (born [[:en:1303|1303]]). * Shōkyō 2nd year / Genkō 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1333|1333]] [[:en:July 4|July 4]]) – [[:en:Hōjō Sadaaki|Hōjō Sadakazu]], the 15th Shikken of the Kamakura shogunate (born [[:en:1278|1278]]). * [[:en:Ryakuō|Ryakuō]] 1st year / [[:en:Engen|Engen]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1338|1338]] [[:en:June 10|June 10]]) – [[:en:Kitabatake Akiie|Kitabatake Akiie]], a military commander ({{ill|Busho (Rank)|ja|武将|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Busho (Rank)|qq=}}) (born [[:en:1318|1318]]). * [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 14th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1586|1586]] [[:en:July 8|July 8]]) – [[:en:Hachisuka Masakatsu|Hachisuga Masakatsu]], a military commander (born [[:en:1526|1526]]). * [[:en:Tenna|Tenna]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1682|1682]] [[:en:June 27|June 27]]) – [[:en:Ikeda Mitsumasa|Ikeda Mitsumasa]], lord of the Okayama Domain in Bizen (born [[:en:1609|1609]]). * [[:en:Hōei|Hōei]] 7th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1710|1710]] [[:en:June 18|June 18]]) – {{ill|Kawai Sōrō|ja|河合曾良|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kawai Sōrō|qq=}}, a haiku poet and one of the disciples of Shōmon Jūtetsu (born [[:en:1649|1649]]). * [[:en:Kansei|Kansei]] 11th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1799|1799]] [[:en:June 25|June 25]]) – [[:en:Asada Goryu|Asada Gōritsu]], an astronomer (born [[:en:1734|1734]]).
